name: Studio in leafy Nieuwendam
summary: Our place is a peaceful hidden oasis, a truly unique spot.    It comprises a former fisherman's cottage with a more recently built studio and a large garden with terrace by the water. It is located down a beautiful green path, off the famous Nieuwendammerdijk, hidden away from the hustle, bustle, noise and smells of Amsterdam.
space: The studio is located in the annexe.  It comprises a private bedroom and bathroom,  and a comfortable sitting area and study.  Also there is a washing machine and dryer are there too, which is shared with the house and  we need to use occasionally during the day.
notes: Whilst there are no cooking facilities in the studio,  you can always make tea or coffee and warm a microwave meal if you wish.  There are several takeout and eating possibilities within 5 minutes of the house.
transit: The centre of the city is 15 minutes by bike and a free ferry or 20 minutes by public transport.  Bus 35 takes you to the metro Noorderpark and the metro 52 onwards to Central Station.  We may be able to lend you a bike: please ask!

house_rules: We take our shoes off indoors and would appreciate it if our guests would (where possible) do the same.   We recycle:- great if you wish to do this too.
interaction: Whilst we are not there in person our neighbours are all very friendly and will gladly answer any questions or help you with a problem.
access: You have  the house and garden fully to yourself.  There is also a gardenhouse-annexe, where we do laundry, keep the spare bedding and linen and other personal items.  This only is not included in the let.
name: Picturesque family house with a great garden
summary: Hansel en Gretel Cottage with sunny garden in green heart of Nieuwendam: fabulous  family stay close to all the sights and sounds of Amsterdam. Our house with a large garden and water front terrace. The garden is secluded and quiet and very pleasant in the summer sunshine.   For children there is a trampoline and swings and a good sized lawn.  There are two dining areas, one by the water and one by the house, perfect to enjoy a drink,  bbq or other meal.
space: This beautiful former fisherman's cottage, a classic 'Zaanse-stijl huisje'   is 200 years old and combines its serene and scenic location with an cosy, and homely interior with open beams and natural materials.  The spacious kitchen has a large table for enjoying meals together, which can be prepared using the oven, grill, gas hob, fridge, freezer and microwave. The lounge is separate and has sitting area, TV, games table with 4 chairs and piano.  From the lounge patio doors lead out into the sunny garden, which backs onto water and is a fantastic spot for absorbing the summer sunshine. The bedrooms are in the long and cosy upper floor, with the double bedroom at one end of the upstairs and the two single bedrooms located at the other end.  The single bedroom with single child's bed needs to be walked through to reach the second one with two beds, making our house most suitable for families.  The bathroom is located on the ground floor, and is warm and spacious with  toilet, washbasin,
notes: Wandering around the garden is a chicken and her chicks, and inside there's an aquarium.  We have three ducks: they now live on the water behind the house, though may come begging !   A handful of food on the tray will make them very happy!  They will also eat out of your hand, it tickles!   We leave food available; the chicken too is happy for a few handfuls of food in their coop every morning.
transit: Bus 32 takes you within 10 minutes to Amsterdam Central Station in the heart of Amsterdam.  By bike and ferry it takes just 15 minutes to reach the centre.  The North-South metro line is about to open as we write, with stations at the Noorderpark and Buikslotermeerplein.

house_rules: Sharing is caring. Sharing a house with other people and sharing a neighourhood means making sure everyone is ok. The rules are based on that and common sense. So please: - Lock windows and doors when you leave the house. - Quiet time after 23.00 Sundays-Thursdays and after midnight Friday and Saturday - If you keep food in the bedrooms put it in a container - we don't want mice! Just ask me if you need a container. - No smoking indoors. - This room is a legal rent and the municipality of Amsterdam makes hosts keep a guest register including the ID, name and address of all guests. You'll need to sign this when you arrive. - Anyone who parties too hard and then throws up in the house loses the 100 euro deposit. Know your limits!
interaction: Happy to help you get set up for your visit to this amazing city! This is my full-time home, although I have an office job and a partner in Utrecht where I spend a couple of nights a week, so you'll certainly see me around some of the time. When I'm out and about I'll be just a phone call away if you have questions. The main thing is for you to feel right at home and just do your own thing!
access: Kitchen, dining area, garden.
name: Cosy home 15 mins from vibrant city centre!
summary: Our place is a cosy 1930s home in a quiet residential area so you'll get a good night's sleep. Excellent access to the centre - the metro station is  700metres away and it's just 1 stop to Central Station. Nearby attractions are the stunning waterside Eye film museum, the Amsterdam Tower with amazing views and rooftop swing and the NDSM site for festivals and hip restaurants. Or head north to enjoy beautiful, quaint fishing villages and swim in the IJsselmeer lake.
space: The house is 3 storeys - with the kitchen and toilet on the ground floor, my bedroom and the guest room on the first floor, and a large bathroom on the second floor. Children are welcome, the house is safe for children who can use stairs safely. Amsterdam is well known for its narrow buildings and steep stairs. Children need to hold on to the banisters. Adults too!  - There's a lounge area in the sunny front yard where you can enjoy the sunshine or smokers can smoke, and a playground 150 meters away. - Good cooking facilities - oven, induction cooker, microwave. The kitchen is well stocked so you can cook your food without having to buy basics like salt, pepper, oil, vinegar, herbs and spices.
notes: It might be useful to know that because the rooms are small the bed is 120 cm wide. This is used as a double bed in the Netherlands, in the US it's known as a three-quarter. Bedding and towels are provided.
transit: Parking is on the street and costs 1.40 euros per hour from 09.00-19.00. The new North-South metro means you're at central station in less than 15 minutes and the famous Albert Cuyp market in 20. From the house you can walk700 metres through the park to the metro or walk 1 minute to the bus stop (3 minute bus ride to metro). Or take the bus to the free ferry that crosses from behind central station 24/7 - great option if you're going by bike.

summary: Delightful modern and sunny apartment right in the heart of Amsterdam. Centrally located, very quiet, modern, topfloor 2-bdrm apartment (110 m2) . With elevator and canal view. Perfect for couples or max. 4 guests who don't like stairs.
space: Our apartment is located 5 minutes away from Central Station by tram. It is modern, spacious and bright, with elevator and stunningviews. The living is south-east facing with windows over the entire length of the living room. It overlooks a spacious green inside garden and a quiet canal. Apart from a modern living with a great sofa, our home offers two large noise free bedrooms, one with a luxurious king-size and a second bedroom with a double sofa-bed and in addition extra high sleeper. Our bathroom with two mirrors and and two washing tables has an  incredible lush shower that you do not want to get out of. The appartement is modern and setup in Feng shui style and is superclean. We offer full amenities, washing machine and dryer, a dishwasher, flatscreen with extra, apps, TV channels, netflix, football (soccer) and F1 channels and wifi high speed internet.  We will be elsewhere during your stay. Location: - 2 minutes from the old town center  - 2m fun bike rental  for eur 15/day. -
notes: You can text through airbnb, email or call, we always aim to respond within an hour.
transit: You can easily cycle everywhere from this wonderful location, but if you're not in the mood to cycle, there is tram stop Rietlanden just 50 meters from our apartment. If you arrive by car, a P&P is just 1 stop by tram ahead, or we can include garage parking under our apartment building for an additional fee.

name: Cosy, lake sided family home in Amsterdam with garden
summary: Welcome to our lovely North-side family home. Enjoy the lovely green, calm parts of Amsterdam.  Our home is perfectly suitable for families and is located in a very kid friendly neighbourhood and lovely authentic Amsterdam streets, just above the centre of the city. It comes with a garden on the lake that is private to yourselves, just like our garden/outside posessions. All free to use. Our home comes with a kitchen, several beds including three single and one double bed and a bathroom with bathtub.
space: Our home is perfectly suitable for families with kids. It has several bedrooms divided over different floors. There is a large, open kitchen free to use and whilst looking over the greener parts of Amsterdam. There is a bathroom with bathub upstairs to be found. The garden is private to yourselves and you are very welcome to make use of it. The late behind our home is lovely, especially during the summer period. Feel free to use our garden essentials: kano, surfboard, BBQ, hammock, swing etc. It is totally kid friendly and very calm for an Amsterdam home. Our home will really make you fall in love with the Nothern side of Amsterdam.
transit: There is a metro and bus connection directly from the Central Station that will take you here within 10-15 minutes. Also a ferry crosses the water that divides Amsterdam city centre with Amsterdam North. Our private parking place is available for our guests.

name: Cozy room in the greenest part of Berlin
space: Located next to the biggest park in Berlin Tiergarten with the biggest zoo in Europe on the Spree river bank. Calm and safe area. S-bahn metro station Bellevue and U-bahn station Hansaplatz are in 2 minutes walking. 15 minutes by bus to the Tegel airport. You can take even a boat just nearby. There are cafes, bars and supermarkets around. Easy access to all tourist attractions, including Brandenburger Tor, Berlin Victory Column, Checkpoint Charlie & Potsdamer Platz. Buses (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) , TXL. You can take Berlin's sightseeing bus next to the Berlin Victory Column in 15 minutes walking, which makes it a perfect location for tourists. LGBTQ friendly. There is everything necessary in the apartment, you can use the equipped kitchen and the living room with a balcony. There are two elevators in the building.
notes: I mostly work from home. My boyfriend Diego and I wake up very early and go to sleep very early too. We may use the juicer at 6am, but this is all the noise you will hear from us. We both love running and biking and appreciate other sports lovers to stay with us. Registration number 01/Z/AZ/ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb)

name: Gezellige woning voor gezin met grote tuin!
summary: Een leuke woning voor een gezin met een grote tuin op het zuiden in een gezellige en oude buurt in Amsterdam. Gratis parkeren in de hele buurt en rechtstreekse verbinding vanaf Schiphol. Je bent zo in het centrum van Amsterdam of de Hollandse natuur. Alleen geschikt voor families. Maximaal 2 volwassenen met kinderen.
space: Het huis heeft 3 slaapkamers, waarvan in 1 slaapkamer een tweepersoonsbed staat, in 1 kamer alle benodigdheden voor een baby 0-3 jaar aanwezig zijn (ledikant, commode, triptrap stoel, enz.) en 1 kamer geheel leeg is en kan worden benut met een luchtbed of reisledikant. De keuken is geheel nieuw en beschikt over alles wat je nodig zou kunnen hebben: 4-pits elektrische kookplaat, grote oven, grote koelkast (met 3 vriesvakken), een cooker-kraan, een magnetron, vaatwasser en een nieuwe kwaliteit koffiemachine. Ook is er op de eerste verdieping een wasmachine en drogeraanwezig.  Veder is het gehele huis voorzien van vloerverwarming, waarmee ook in de zomer het huis gekoeld kan worden. Tot slot heeft het huis een 100m2 tuin op het zuiden met een grote eettafel om aan te ontbijten, een ruime zithoek om s â€™avonds in de ondergaande zon te zitten en volop gras voor kinderen om in te spelen. In de tuin is verder ook een pizzaoven aanwezig om zelf pizzaâ€™s in te bakken.
notes: Het is een gezinswoning dus het is geschikt voor een stel met kinderen. Dus geschikt voor 4 personen maar niet voor 4 volwassenen.
transit: Door de komst van de Noord/Zuidlijn (nieuwe metroverbinding) is de verbinding met Schiphol ook ideaal geworden. Binnen 20-25 minuten arriveer je op het metrostation 5 minuten bij ons vandaan. Ons huis grenst aan een plein (Purmerplein) waar je o.a. een bakker, slager, groenteman en een aantal verschillende restaurants en eetgelegenheden kunt vinden. Ook het hier beroemde cafÃ© â€˜Het Sluisjeâ€™ aan de Nieuwendammerdijk is op nog geen 5 minuten loopafstand. Tot slot kun je op de fiets binnen 5 minuten fietsen genieten van de oer-Hollandse polder ten noorden van Amsterdam, met uiteraard veel dijkjes, kanaaltjes en molens.

interaction: We will be traveling while we are away, but we are contactable by phone or email and we have someone in Amsterdam who you can turn to should you have any problems.
name: Quaint Dutch house & garden, free parking & bikes
summary: After a day in central Amsterdam come home to the rustic village feel of this house overlooking fields of animals and wild birds.  The cosy living/dining room has double doors opening onto a patio & lawn which catches the sun all day and is a perfect spot for an evening barbeque.  The house itself has two upstairs bedrooms (one double, one single) and a bathroom with a bath.  Running the length of the garden is another flat with a double bedroom, childrenâ€™s playroom and bathroom with a shower.
space: Built in 1915, this classic Dutch house has an open living/dining room with French windows opening out onto a patio and lawn at one end and a bay window looking out onto a little front garden with a canal at the other.  The livingroom has an old fashioned cosy feel, with a sofa & chaise long, a comfy arm chair, a beautiful old desk and a wood burning stove.  The dining room has a dining table set up for 5 people flanked by an antique bookshelf. The kitchen is fully equipped with fridge, freezer, microwave, dishwasher and oven.  And the storage room has a washing machine and drier.  Both the kitchen and the living/dining room open out onto the patio and lawn.  The garden gets sun all day long and comes with a table for 5 and a barbeque. Up the typically steep Dutch stairs (with a handy banister) you find the master bedroom overlooking the garden.  At the other end of the landing is a single bedroom with a stunning view over the fields.  This room contains a single bed and a babyâ€™s cot.
transit: Bikes make getting round Amsterdam a breeze and we have 4 adult bikes (2 of which have baby seats attached) and 2 children's bikes (for 10 year olds) available for guests to borrow.   If biking is not your thing then the bus stop is 5 minutes away.    To get into the centre of Amsterdam the easiest and quickest way is a 7 minute bike ride (or 10 minute bus & 5 minute walk) to NDSM warf followed by a magical 15 minute free ferry into Central Station, right in the heart of the city.  The ferry ride is something I would recommend to anyone visiting the city.   If you want to get out and see the rest of the Netherlands, you can catch a train to pretty much anywhere from Central Station or Sloterdijk Station. If you are driving, you aren't far from the ring-road (A10) round Amsterdam from which you can go for day trips to Rotterdam, The Hague, Delft, the beach and more.  All within an hour's drive or less.

name: One of a kind! Amazing boat with beautiful view
summary: Welcome on board! The 'Emma' is an amazing ship in the east of Amsterdam. The boat is new and no less than 40 meters long and 6 meters wide. A lot of space, especially outside on the deck - there's a big sun bathing area, with a gorgeous view on the IJ. You can enjoy your morning coffee on the front deck of the boat, or join us in the back close to the water. One part of the boat is for you, the other part is mine and we could run in to each other sometimes. As the Dutchies say: 'Gezellig'!
space: The boat is new and has lots of space. You will come in through the front door, go down the stairs and on your right you will find your part of the boat. There's a small living room with lounge area, tv, dining/reading/working area. You don't have to share that space with anyone else. There are two big bedrooms, one with a double bed (160 x 200 cm) and one with a single bed (80 x 190 cm). There are two bathrooms as well, one for each bedroom. One bathroom has a toilet and a shower, the other one has a toilet and a bathtub. I'm sure you will enjoy your stay at my place.
transit: There's a busstop only a minute away, the bus will take you to different places in the city. The city centre is about 30 minutes away by bus, 15 minutes by bike.

name: beautiful apartment in the center of Amsterdam
description: The lively nightspot and market square Nieuwmarkt, found in the old city centre just east of the Red Light District, has been a centre for commerce and socialising in Amsterdam since the 17th century. Created by filling in the surrounding canals, the square's location just inside the old city gate made it a popular spot for traders and shoppers looking for fresh produce. Today, Nieuwmarkt still holds a daily market as well as an organic fare market on Saturdays, but arguably its biggest draw is the amount of cafÃ©s, restaurants and coffeeshops that surround it, making this square a perfect place to spend a sunny day sitting on a terrace. The Nieuwmarkt metro stop can be found on the square, which caused quite a bit of protest during its construction but now serves as one of the city's most central and most used stops on the metro service.

name: Cosy family home near industrial NDSM wharf
summary: Welcome to the coziest 'village' of Amsterdam. This 'village' is a historic part of Amsterdam. Decades ago it used to be home to workers from the nearby NDSM ship wharf. Nowadays the wharf is one of Amsterdam's most popular hot-spots due to its industrial feel, bars and cafe's overlooking the water, a huge flee market and art galleries.  Enjoy a ride on the free ferry which will take you to Amsterdam Central Station within 15 minutes.  The neighborhood is also near a wonderful nature parc.
space: Our house is a family house. It has a private front door leading to the cosy living room. The living room is bright and has loads of art and plants. We have a long wooden dining table which is great for sharing meals, reading newspapers or getting dome work done. There is a toilet and a pantry on the ground floor as well. Our kitchen is fully equipped as we love cooking! The kitchen back door leads to our back yard which is sunny all afternoon! Upstairs you will find the bathroom, bedroom and spare room. A flight up is the attic, which can be used to do some laundry if necessary.
transit: We provide 2 bicycles if needed. There is a bus stop just around the corner. To take the ferry to the city center, take a 10 minute walk to the wharf.

Balcony has sun from the morning till afternoon.

Lots of Sunshine here!:) The kitchen has got everything you could need to make a lovely meal..
transit: The great thing about Amsterdam is that everything is within biking distance; you will easily find a bike rental nearby. If you prefer to take public transport, the nearest tram stop is only 200 meters away. Amsterdam central station is a 15 minute walk.

summary: When you are looking for a great place close to the city centre but outside the noise of it all, this is the place to be.  Sleeping up to 4 guests in this great surroundings, this fantastic holiday home makes the perfect choice for your stay in Amsterdam!
space: This gorgeous apartment is excellently designed with your comfort in mind. A warm inviting living space features nice flooring throughout and deliciously contemporary furniture.  An elegant dining table and chairs enable you to make mealtimes comfortable and itâ€™s of course the perfect time to plan tomorrowâ€™s adventures in town together. Prepare favourite recipes from home or why not try a little Dutch cooking with local spices from the nearby convenience stores and supermarkets. The fantastic fitted kitchen is packed with all the equipment you need to create something delicious. The pretty bedroom is stylishly presented and features unfussy tones to encourage restful sleep and there is ample storage for your belongings.  The apartment also features a private bathroom. Enjoy the outdoor space!
notes: Guests I look for: - Respectful of neighbours (keep level of noise down) and my place - Non-smokers (or smokers that smoke outside and clean up their cigarettes) - Above 30 when in a group of 3/4 - Any age if staying as a responsible and clean couple At time of departure:  Leave the home as tidy as you found it. make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean.  all keys must be returned upon departure. Failure to do so will incur a replacement fee. Please leave the keys behind you on the table, and close the door behind you. In case the door is not locked when you close it, lock the door and put the keys in the mailbox.  Guests must immediately inform the host of all defects in the apartment and damages that occur in the apartment.

interaction: We wonÂ´t be there when you stay in our house but of course you can reach us by phone if you have questions. We have a second small house on the property where our 18-year old son lives. He is there - sometimes - and you can of course reach out to him.
access: Our guests get our whole house to use on their own.  You have access to the garden which you can use as well. There is a swing, a children's play house in the trees and a patio faced south.
name: House to explore Berlin or relax within nature
summary: We are an open minded family of 5; living at the border of Berlin. When we are away, we offer our beautiful house to people from all over the world. Only 10-15 minutes walk away from the trainstation you get easy right into the city of Berlin.  At the same time our place is great to relax with lakes and forest only some steps away. We love to get in contact with our guests if possible to assist them with their stay. As we lived some time abroad we are always interested in other people & mindsets
space: We live in Erkner, which is a small town right at the border to Berlin. You can have a great stay here as the town offers everything you need: more than 5 supermarkets, a cinema, some shops and restaurant. The area is perfect for cycling, walking, swimming (in the lake) as we live near the forest and three lakes. If you want to explore Berlin, the train/ public transport takes you to the very centre in 16 minutes (Ostkreuz), 20 minutes (Ostbahnhof), 25 minutes (Alexanderplatz).
transit: If you stay with a car you can park it in front of our house. You can the use the public transport from the station Erkner. It is approx. 10-15 minutes walk from our house or 1 stop with the bus.  From the station Erkner leaves a normal train every 10-20 minutes towards various stations in Berlin.  Another train ( fast train) leaves every 30 minutes and takes you to these stations as well. The price for a day ticket is only 7.70 EUR and you can use any kind of public transport within Berlin till 3am the next morning!

This space also doubles nicely as laptop-friendly workspace for those who are traveling for business. The second bedroom is complete with 2 single beds of 9

space: Tucked away in a quiet street in the eastern district of central Amsterdam, Residence 85 is a slick apartment building that offers 8 airy apartments with quality yet understated furnishings and fixtures. We put emphasis on the balances between the natural textures and decorative accents with the minimal design and neutral tones of Scandinavian aesthetics. We highlighted the historic bones of the building with warm and modern finishes to give you a homey, cosmopolitan boutique apartment. Apartment K offers 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms (separate toilet and separate shower).  The apartment is located on the first floor and presents a kitchen space, dining area and living room. This space also doubles nicely as laptop-friendly workspace for those who are traveling for business. The first and third bedrooms each contain a single bed of 90x200 cm and a wardrobe, which is perfect for business travelers or friends who want their own space.   The second bedroom is complete with 2 single beds of 9

name: Beautiful apartment near Rembrandt and Vondelpark
summary: Beautiful apartment near Rembrandt and Vondelpark This completely renovated apartment is situated at the Rembrandtpark and near the city centre and Vondelpark. The neighbourhood is called "oud-west", an upcoming trendy area with restaurants and bars. The apartment itself is luxurious with a touch of an industrial look. There is a balcony (sunny side), elevator. And a great view from the 12th floor, you can see the whole city! Near Schiphol, public transport and supermarkets.

name: Vintage & Architecture in buzzing NDSM-area
summary: Come and experience the city of Amsterdam from the north and sunny side of the river IJ. This is where a former industrial area is transforming into a vibrant residential and creative hub. Ground floor private studio with vintage design vibe in stunning architectural and sustainable new building. With free parking and outside patio in trendy Amsterdam-North and the hip 'n happening NDSM-area. Only 15 minutes from city center. Walking distance from lots of diners and coffee/breakfast bars.
space: The studio is approx. 36 square meters. It has a high ceiling (4m20) and sitting window in the front. The sleeping area has normal ceiling hight (2m60). The studio has oak parquet floors with floorheating and cooling. A marble mosaic floor in the hallway. There is a 'Fresh-R' unit that provides for clean air in de studio and bathroom. - 1 double bed (1m40) - high speed wifi internet - kitchen with a stove and oven, fridge/freezer, dishwasher, Nespresso coffee machine, toaster and more - dining table with 3 seats and two foldable chairs for sitting outside. - 1 sofa, extendable for long legs or laying down. - separate bathroom with toilet, sink and shower Toegang voor gasten As our guest you have access to the hallway that leads to the studio and your private bathroom. There are foldable chairs to sit outside in the sunny  front or in the back. There's a park and canal in front of the house where it's nice to swim in summertime. house_rules: As we live in a very nice community please respect the neighborhood and the people living here. Our neighbors have 2 kids, so please respect their privacy by not making too much noise after 22:00h at night. Strictly forbidden to have a party, smoke, or use drugs. If so, we do not refund the deposit. Please respect the environment, the water around you and all it's animals.
interaction: Most of the times we are out when we have Airbnb guests, but our neighbors will take care of everything when there are questions.
name: Unique floating, sustainable waterhouse/boathouse.
summary: Unique, brand new floating house in the upcoming hip & vibrant Northern part of Amsterdam. Only 10 minutes away from the city center and very easy to reach. We are part of the "Schoonschip"- community with 46 households and are the most sustainable floating neighborhood in Europe! We are very proud on this unique project and love to tell and show you more.
space: We have a luxury, brand new and fully equipped kitchen with a big fridge, freezer, microwave, steam oven, induction stove, tap with boiling water and dish wasser. We have two high chairs for small kids. The kitchen has an outside terrace overlooking the water. There's a big bbq (kamado)  for a nice evening dinner.  The bathroom has a bath tube, a special  high-tech  touchscreen shower with a 80% water-saving-system and a sink with two taps. There are towels and a blow dryer. We have a vacuum-toilet that hardly uses water to flush.  We have one seperate bedroom which we use as room for our baby, so it has a crib and a changing table, but also has  a extendable bed for two-persons. This door can be closed.  Our own, large two- persons bed is only seperated by a big curtain for privacy. There is also an extra baby bed.  For your comfort there's a large TV with Netflix and over a 100 internationals channels in the living room. For the audio-freaks we have a beautiful hifi set where you can
notes: Please note that this place is suitable for a family of max 4. We would not recommend more than 4 people, cause we can't accommodate beds for more than 4 adults.  Feel free to read all our reviews about our former house so you can convince yourself about the right choice ;-)  Feel also free to ask any questions.
transit: Its easy to reach our place by car (paid parking from Monday-Saturday, a full day is â‚¬10 max). There are still places for free parking a bit further away in the area, please ask on arrival. Busses, ferries and the subway all take you in several minutes from Amsterdam Central Station to our place. By bike you reach the hotspots in the area within 10 minutes, and also all ferries that take you to nearly any part of Amsterdam in no time. We also have a very nice park in walking-distance.

name: BEAUTIFUL APPARTMENT IN THE CENTER OF AMSTERDAM
summary: Treat yourself to this beautiful and comfortable apartment with a lovely balcony. Close to the famous westerpark with bars, restaurants and a movie cinema. located next to the city centre, Anne Frank house 15 minutes, Dam square 20min , Jordaan/Canal District 5min and the red light district Soft towels, drinks & cookies, kingsize bed all await you to help make your Amsterdam stay a special experience.
space: if you are looking for a very convenient place for 1 or 2 with everything you need for a great stay in Amsterdam, this is your place. It is a charming appartment with a balcony (55m2), newly renovated bathroom and separate toilet. You will have a real comfortable bed. space: This apartment is designed for people who enjoy silence and tranquility, for people who want to rest, it is not a party apartment. The apartment has all the amenities, bathroom with tub, fully equipped kitchen, heating, etc.

name: Comfortable studio in Amsterdam!

name: Dare to be different, private place, for You & You
summary: A sailboat moored on an idyllic and quiet canal about 10 minutes by public transport from the centre. It is equiped with a small kitchenette and a tiny separate toilet as well as a bedroom for two. These two small beds can be turned into one double bed. There is a table with two benches where you can sit and overlook the canal. Included are two membershipcards to the gym to take a shower. There's NO WIFI NOR electricity. Ideal for  couples. Plse read the description carefully before booking.
space: The boat is cosy and definitely more for a romantic weekend away from the average experience. Yes you will either love it or hate it. You will have the place to yourselves. Mind the standing height is 185 cm. The boat is a bit like camping: the lights are usb charged and there is no electricity nor WIFI. So it is really not for those who are hooked on their mobile, or like luxury.  There are/is  a box bed for two (whicch can be two single beds or one double), there is a tiny toilet, a kitchenette where there are two burners no tapwater (drinkingwater will be supplied for the first day or so, ten liters. you can pass by my house to fill the jerrycan anytime you like btw when it is empty). There is coffee and tea supplied. You get a membership for a nearby gym so you can take a shower as well as if you like exercise.  What you get is an adventure which you either love or hate, there is no inbetween. At least you will definitely have a story when you are back home. It is a place for the m
notes: Mind you have to be able to climb on board. There are steps inside as well. The boatis best for two people, like a couple or close friends. There is NO electricity I provide you with a powerbank but plse bring one yourself as well. If you have a complaint turn to me and I will do my utmost to fix it or work something out. Yes it can be cold during Autumn and Winter as well as in early Spring. Yes you have to be daring, it can be heaven though.
transit: The tram at only 200 meters away from the boat leads you straight into the city and goes all the way to the Central Station. From the airport it is about twenty minutes by public transport.

name: Spacious & light apartment in cosy neighborhood
summary: Welcome in Amsterdam East! I'm a cultural anthropologist, frequent traveler and I'd love to welcome you to this spacious and light apartment. It's located in a quiet, green and cosy street near the Oosterpark, only 10 minutes away from the city centre. It has a warm, earthly and artistic energy. The place, with a bathtub and sunny balcony will allow you to enjoy Amsterdam in comfort and style. When around, I'd also be more than happy to show you around this vibrant neighborhood.
transit: Although Amsterdam is best visited by bicycle, this apartment has a free inside car parking spot. Also, both bus, tram, train and metro are in walking distance and will bring you anywhere you like!
description: Welcome in Amsterdam East! I'm a cultural anthropologist, frequent traveler and I'd love to welcome you to this spacious and light apartment. It's located in a quiet, green and cosy street near the Oosterpark, only 10 minutes away from the city centre. It has a warm, earthly and artistic energy. The place, with a bathtub and sunny balcony will allow you to enjoy Amsterdam in comfort and style. When around, I'd also be more than happy to show you around this vibrant neighborhood. This neighborhood is called 'Transvaal' and has many South-African streetnames. The famous Easterpark is just a five minutes walk away and around the corner you find the 'Beukenplein' with nice restaurants and coffee places. Although Amsterdam is best visited by bicycle, this apartment has a free inside car parking spot. Also, both bus, tram, train and metro are in walking distance and will bring you anywhere you like!

name: Spacious and bright apartment (93m2)
summary: Our spacious and bright apartment (93m2) in the Rivierenbuurt is perfect for 3 persons. Good to know: we have an extra roommate, our very friendly cat Henk. Flexible checkin earlier or later is possible if we're available, just ask me!
space: Our house (3 pers/92m2) is located in the popular area Rivierenbuurt, a quiet neighbourhood next to the Amstel and near lots of nice spots. Perfect with kids! Also very convenient for business travellers, as 'de Rivierenbuurt' is close to the business district Zuidas, World Trade Centre, convention centre Rai and the main traffic ring. The apartment is on the 2nd and 3rd (top) floor and has 2 balcony's with all day sun! There is free wireless internet and a TV. Our living room provides you with a large couch, a kitchen with cooking island and a dinner/work table. For kids we have a playpen, babycrib, 2 chairs and lots of toys.  On the 3rd floor we have a bathroom, toilet and 2 rooms. One bedroom with a large double bed (1.80 m x 2 m) and one room with a toddler bed or for a third adult: a good matress on the floor. The bedrooms are very quiet. One bedroom has been provided with a large van.
transit: Rivierenbuurt is located in between train and metro stations Amsterdam Amstel and Amsterdam Rai and easily accessible by tram 4 and 12. It takes 15 min to the city centre, that is: Leidseplein, Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum, the Vondelpark and the historic canals. It's also nice to walk to town; especially to stroll along the river Amstel (for example 40 min to the above museums). But of course the best way to explore Amsterdam is by bike! Then it takes only 10 min to the citycentre. You can get rental bikes nearby, at Amstel Fietspoint. You can park a car in front of our house (Monday-Saturday: 4,50 euro per hour, 18 euro for a day pass, Sunday free). Travelling from Schiphol: * 20 min by taxi * 30 min by train to Amsterdam Amstel, from there it's 10-15 min walk. * 10 min by train to Amsterdam RAI, but from there walking is to far. Take bus 62 to Victoriepln (10 min) and from there it's a 10 min walk to our apartment. If we're available we can pick you up at Schiphol.

The box is inspired by the economic effectivization of space, present in cities such as Hong Kong, where the free market has been successfully deregulated: here 200.000 people live in so-called â€œcoffin homesâ€: the size of your home is equivalent to the size of your body.

Me and my wife only live in the aparment for half a year but found ourselves during weekends  quite often at friends and family, letting our beloved house all alone. So we felt like sharing it with other couples (or friends). Feel very welcome as long you are as kind for the house as it will for you.
space: Spacious living room, diner table, full kitchen with equipment. Please note that our bath does not give bubbles, we only use it as a shower.
transit: Trains on station Muiderpoort on 5 minute bike, trams on 2 minute walking, plenty parking spots and even a P+R closeby for free parking.

name: Cozy family home in Berlin suburb
summary: Our house is situated in a residential family arear in the eastern suburbs of Berlin. The area is great for kids and families and very quiet. However, the U5 and S5 are in walking distance and hence its only 20 min to Friedrichshain and 25 to Aleksanderplatz. The house has three floors a small garden and a nice and sunny winter garden.
space: The house has three floors a small garden and a nice and sunny winter garden. On the first floor is a guest WC, the open kitchen and a large living room. The couch in the living room is foulding into an additional bed for 2.  From the living room you can step out to the winter garden and the garden. On the first floor you find the bathroom and a bed room. It hosts a loft bed for 2 (standard 1.40 m wide) and a sleeping area below the loft beed for 2  (standard 1.40 m wide). The floor hosts another room (our bedroom) which we will look to store our personal belongings).  On the top floor is a studio. You find a working and a paying area there, but you could also put the two mattresses from the bedroom here to have seperate sleeping areas. The house has floor heating, which makes it cozy and comfortible.  As we have a small daughter, the house is childproof (protection in plugs, protection for the stairs, etc.)
transit: U5 and S5 are a 10 min walk away. Frome the station you reach Alexanderplatz in 25 min and Friedrichshain in 20 min.

name: Beautiful apt in Amsterdam next to the Jordaan
summary: This very light and perfect situated apartment, is my home and your home away from home. Spread over 60 sqm it's a light and airy space - come experience Amsterdam from here!
space: There is a modern, well equipped kitchen with windows looking on to the pretty Hugo de Grootplein. To the front of the apartment you will also find the large diningtable with the same view. The livingroom has a large sofa where you can chill after a long day in the city. The TV has a Netflix & Videoland account whitch you can use. In the bedroom there is a really comfortable double bed. Next to the bedroom there is a cozy balcony which is completely isolated from the busy Amsterdam.
transit: Just in front of the apartment is a tram station. From here you can explore the whole city. Also it's possible to rent  a bike across the street.

name: Spacious renovated apartment in de Pijp + balcony!
summary: Recently (June 2019)  renovated apartment in the heart of the best neighborhood of Amsterdam, De Pijp! Very big living room with equipped kitchen, big kitchen table (10 seats available), comfortable couch and a big television. You can also enter the balcony here, where you find a nice lounge. The bathroom has just been renovated as well. There is one bedroom available with a small 2-pers bed (120x200 cm). We could put a big air mattress in the living room where another 2 adults can sleep.
transit: Metrostation 'De Pijp' within 5 minutes walk.

The apartment is centrally located in de so called "hoofddorppleinbuurt' area. In between the Surinamerplein and the Hoofddorpplein. Only 2 minutes walking from the Vondelpark and nearby are several trendy cafes and restaurants where you may go for drinks, lunch or dinner. summary: Gezellig appartementje in een fijne buurt, gelegen dicht bij het centrum van Amsterdam en perfect te bereiken met openbaar vervoer. Een stille, rustige slaapkamer. Alle voorzieningen zijn aanwezig, ook kunt u heerlijk gebruik maken van het balkon. Er is bovendien een poes aanwezig (Charlotte), die het leuk vindt om met je te spelen :)! Er is een mooi park op 2 minuten loopafstand, zo ook de tram die rechtstreeks naar het centrum rijdt.

name: Bright, spacious and newly renovated family house
summary: Bright, spacious and newly renovated family house near the Amsterdam Forest and the Zuidas. Luxurious kitchen and bathroom with free parking space in front of the house. Only 15 minutes away from the city centre (by bike/car/public transport). Free bikes are available!
space: Our beautiful and stylish house is located in a nice residential area, just outside the city center of Amsterdam. We have a large, garden facing kitchen with all the appliances you need. There is a Gaggenau dishwasher, oven, steam oven, fridge, as well as a slow juicer and a Nespresso machine. Great to enjoy your fresh juice in the morning. The kitchen is perfect if you like to cook, or just to enjoy your meal at a table that seats up to eight near the fireplace. You can reach the garden via lofty windows. The living area is at the first floor and has a big sofa and TV, where you can relax. You can also find the study and one of the bedrooms at this floor. The other three bedrooms and the bathroom are at the second floor. The bathroom has an extra large bath and a rain shower. Our Italian towels and linen are at your disposal. Since our daughter is one year old, we have quite some things for a baby, such as a chair and toys.

name: Luxury row house in Amsterdam Grachtengordel-West
summary: Unique! A complete CANAL HOUSE renovated in 2016 with a spacious garden and sunny roof terrace (total living space approximately 229m2) at a beautiful (quiet) location on the Singel. The property has been tastefully renovated and has already been placed in two interior magazines. The property consists of 6 floors. You will find the entrance in the basement and from there the garden of more than 14 meters deep can be reached.
space: At the top floor you will find a beautiful and sheltered roof terrace with sunlight all day until late in the evening. The entire building was completely renovated in 2016, with neither expense nor trouble being spared. The property is equipped with 4 bedrooms and 4 bathrooms, a separate central heating boiler for the two lower floors and the four upper floors and a pump which ensures a good water pressure at the top floors. Although the building is only 3 meters wide, you will not notice it that much due to the convenient lay-out. The property contains high ceilings and due to the perfect location there is a lot of light. BASEMENT Through a hard stone staircase from the street you go down a few steps where a double door gives access to the building. At the front part of the basement you will find an original black and white checkered marble floor. There is a sitting area with coffee corner. name: Luxury Appartement in Amsterdam,GrachtengordelZuid
summary: Bright, high and with large windows: a modern and beautifully detailed loft apartment of approximately 167 sqm. An oasis of light and space with a width of over 9 metres and a ceiling height of approximately 3.35 metres. Recently renovated by architect Ruud van Oosterhout with the use of high-quality materials, finishing and detailing. The apartment is very functional yet gives the feeling of living in an art gallery. The property is ideally suited for an art and design lover.
space: The luxury is emphasized by the concept of beautiful materials and finishing, underfloor heating, a fireplace, ceiling-high doors, domotics and excellent insulation. The bedrooms are a haven of peace. The property can be reached from a representative entrance and a lift. The apartment is on one floor and has an intimate terrace at the rear. The front offers a splendid view of a beautiful part of Prinsengracht. Location: The apartment is located on Prinsengracht near Spiegelgracht. Centrally located in relation to Museumplein, the National Museum and the Vondelpark. A lively environment with many nice restaurants, various antique shops, galleries and luxury shops on P. C. Hooftstraat. Favourably located near public transport and easily accessible by car from the A10 orbital motorway and the motorways A1, A2, A4 and A9 (exits S110 and S112 (Wibautstraat)). The metro stop on Vijzelgracht is within walking distance. Specifics: - Freehold land - Fireplace - Completely renovated - Invisible

name: Spacious apartment in hip and upcoming area
summary: The apartment is perfect for two, it is very spacious and has everything you need! The kitchen is fully equipped and has a Nespresso machine for your daily coffee. There is 5G Wi-Fi and you can even watch Netflix on the 65 inch TV! The apartment is very close the center, Artis (the zoo) and Tropen Museum. On a few minutes walking distance you can go to Brouwerij 't Ij, an Amsterdam beer brewery with an authentic windmill. Around the apartment there are many shops, restaurants and coffee bars.
transit: The apartment is a few minutes walking distance from the train station Muiderpoort, from which you can take the train to Schiphol Airport. The train can also take you to Central Station in 5 minutes (one stop), or you can take the bus or tram to get everywhere (for info about public transport use the website/app (Website hidden by Airbnb) Or of course you can also go to Studio Bike, around the corner, and rent bycicles!

space: The flat is very modern and renovated flat. You reach the appartment by elevator.
transit: The location is close by walking to the famous district of Kreuzberg.  Furthermore the flat is pretty much close to everything because its totally central location in city center. The next metro station (tube) is:  Spittelmarkt It is very easy and fast to come around by the metro.

Further you ve the kitchen an the bathroom to use. In the second room I'm living by myself. I'm present during the week after 6 PM. And varing at the weekend. The neighboorhood in the house is very quiet. The neighborrhood in the destrict is pretty quiet, eventhough the location is very close to sight seeing attractions and famous monuments. access: If you're planning on cooking your own meals you can feel free to use essentials like seasoning, oil, etc. Feel free to open the cupboards to find whatever you're looking for (like pots, pans, cutlery, etc.). If there's something you can't find, just ask. There's tea and coffee you can help yourself to, including milk & sugar. Otherwise please shop for your own groceries. There's lots of space in the fridge.
name: Good Vibes In Berlin
summary: I'll be travelling over NYE, so you can stay in my home. :) My apartment is cozy, comfortable, and clean - a good place to retreat, or to get ready to go out & explore Berlin. I'll can give you recommendations for an amazing stay. The place is just 5 minutes away from public transport (trains, subway and busses)! Super quick and easy access to city center, busy going out areas, and shopping areas. The area itself is quiet and residential. There are several grocery stores close by.
space: The space itself is clean and tidy, 420- & queer-friendly. There is a pull-out couch in the living room, which is big & comfortable enough for two. The bedroom has a regular bed. Since this is my apartment and I usually rent it as a shared space, there won't be any closet space unfortunately. I'm renting the apartment while I am travelling.  The apartment itself is pretty cozy - every friend I have over tends to highlight how they feel right at home. There's some nice lighting, tapestries, (loads of) plants and art that contributes to the good vibes of the place. Feel free to use the speakers to listen to some music. There is an Apple TV with a few games and Netflix & Amazon Prime. There's also an Amazon Echo/a speaker for music. I can show you how everything works upon arrival. There's areas to work (desks and tables), too.
notes: Please note that this is a queer-friendly and 420-friendly space, and make sure you are comfortable with that. Don't be fooled by the bad street-lighting walking up to our apartment - Berlin is a pretty dark city, us Germans are very energy efficient. I can assure you that the area is safe. :)
transit: Keep in mind - Berlin is a very large city (it's bigger than New York City) and it is normal to take more than 30 minutes to get to final destinations.  We live in 5 minute walking distance from the train station. Public transportation is amazing here. Trains run every 3-5 minutes and will get you to the city center, shopping areas, going out areas and even the other side of the city (including Potsdam) without having to transfer. You will have access to the S-Bahn, U-Bahn, and busses.  For example: - 15 - 20 mins to Alexanderplatz, Museum island (city center "Mitte") - 5 - 10 mins to going out areas Warschauer StraÃŸe and Ostkreuz (neighborhood Friedrichshain). - 20 - 40 mins to shopping areas (Alexanderplatz, FriedrichstraÃŸe, KurfÃ¼rstendamm) - 20 - 40 minutes to alternative going out areas NeukÃ¶lln and Kreuzberg
